This year, the University of Harvard has set up a new course that allows all first-cycle students to sleep more and fight against the growing Machist trend that involves studying as a caffeine consumption all night.
A professor noted that most students at the best university in the world can't take care of them
This course, designed by Charles Czeisler, Professor of Sleep Medicine at Harvard Medical School and specialist at Brigham and Women's Hospital, is the first of the kind in the United States.
It is after giving a lecture on the effects of sleep deprivation on learning that the idea has come to him
At the end, a student approached me and said, "Why do I have to say this to myself in the last year?"
